Multilotek - is a simulation of a Polish lottery game "Multi Lotek".


Sources with the most up-to-date version of the program can be found at:

    >>>   http://gitorious.org/multilotek   <<<


////////////////// LAYOUT //////////////////

The program consists of five classes:
- mainwindow - shows the window and all of its elements
- drawing - draws the numbers and does all calculations related to it
- statistics - runs statistics of the performed drawings
- export_import - exports the data from the program into a file and imports it back again
- about - shows information about the author of the program

two forms:
- mainwindow form - the main window with drawing, statistics etc.
- about form - a small window with the information about the author of the program

and non-class files:
- globals - contains constant global values, arrays and functions


////////////////// INSTALLATION //////////////////

If you want to compile the application on any platform, make sure you have Qt libraries.
You can download Qt SDK from:
    http://www.qtsoftware.com/downloads

---------------

Easy way: Open the project in Qt Creator and build it. Run the application and have fun!

---------------

Another way:

LINUX
If you prefer using command lines (i.e. on Linux), open a terminal and go to the top level
source directory (usually the same as where this file, README, is located) with this command:

    cd /path/to/source_directory
    
and compile and build the program with these:

    qmake
    make
    
Then you can run the application by typing:

    ./multilotek

Additionally on Linux you can install the application with:

    sudo make install

Now you will find the application in your system menu under the Games category.
Enjoy!

.............

WINDOWS
If you want to build the application on Windows from a terminal, I recommend using
Qt Command Prompt (installed with Qt SDK) and these commands:

    cd path\to\source_directory
    qmake CONFIG+=release
    mingw32-make
    cd release
    multilotek.exe

If you want to launch the compiled program later without the medium of Qt Creator
or the terminal, fo instance from Files Explorer, you have to have these libraries:

    QtCore4.dll, QtGui4.dll, mingw10.dll.

You can find them in the Qt SDK installation folder.
After inserting them into the folder with the executable file or into
C:\Windows\system32, the application will start with no errors.


////////////////// SUPPORTED SYSTEMS //////////////////

The program has been tested on the following systems:

  Windows XP Professional SP3
  Ubuntu 9.04 Jaunty Jackalope 32-bit
  Gentoo

The program should compile and work on any system from a family of Linux, Windows
and MacOS.


////////////////// DEVELOPING THE PROGRAM //////////////////

I encourage  you to further develop my program. You can redistribute and modify it
under the terms of the GPL v3 free software licence, which contents are located
in COPYING file. GPL v3 lets you modify the code in any way you like, but if you want
to publish your modified version of the program, you will have to include the source
codes with changes that you made.

Sources with the most up-to-date version of the program can be found at:

    >>>   http://gitorious.org/multilotek   <<<


You can also translate the program to other languages. A detailed tutorial how to
do it can be found on

    http://doc.qtsoftware.com/4.5/linguist-manual.html

In short:
In order to obtain texts to translate from the source files, use a command:

    lupdate multilotek.pro

Texts are inserted into a file with .ts extension.
You have to open this file in Qt Linguist and translate it.

Then with a command:

    lrelease multilotek.pro

all .ts files are compiled to .qm format and the program includes them inside itself
during a build process.


